A Riveting PsychoDrama Focusing on Dementia, BloodShed, & Murder ! Always Beautiful Scream Queen Debbie Rochon Leads this Talented Ensemble Cast, along with also Lovely Karen White, as well as Kevin White & Joel D. Wynkoop as the Troubled "Bob" .
  Magnificent Melanie Robel makes an All Too Brief Appearance as a CheerLeader in a Diner, where She made my Temperature Rise !!!
There is No Nudity; but a Whimsical Discussion about "Head", as well as a Coupla' Head Detachings .
  I don't mean to Post a Spoiler; But ..........Any Man who Stops Debbie Rochon, from Removing Her Towel, is an Extremely Disturbed Individual, & is Capable of Any Deviant Behavior !!!
  "Stopped Dead" is Well Worth Making a Stop here for !

I didn't think the husband had something to do with it till his wife died, the drive home. and the meat incident. * I only wish I knew how he got the jump on the C.I.A lady and the lady at the end.

Stopped dead was a darker movie than I expected but very much enjoyable. The characters on a vacation to a psychological hell were deep and fully developed. I got the very real sense that the director spent a lot of time drawing out these characters on paper, figuring out their complications and backgrounds and weaknesses. I think it pays off well.  The plot itself had a way of taunting and teasing to an end that should have been obvious to me, but I was kept guessing.  Acting was excellent. Overall a very satisfying movie.
